text: I love that Apple is running an apprenticeship program to bring more people into their company who would otherwise not be in that type of role.  That's a big deal, those programs are an expense for the company that doesn't always pay dividends and is usually pushed off on people to go get that education on their own dime and then come work for their company.  It's a great alternative to college that still offers a lucrative 'college level' salary.  More companies need to do this.  Great show, thank you!

replies.text: I mean... I'm almost 40 now, and I discover quality hip hop all the time. Depends on your taste of course, there are so many types of Hip Hop today.
